  <div class="header-body">
    <h1>Collapse-UI</h1>
    <p>A Modified Custom Bedrock Edition UI to look more Console-style UI.</p>
    <a href="installation.html"><button class="pill" type="button">Download/Installation</button></a>
  </div>
  <div class="header-bottom">
    <div class="bottom-heading">
      <h2>Infos</h2>
      <hr class="gray enableOnMobile">
    </div>
    <div class="elements">
      <div class="element-panel">
        <div class="element-panel-body">
          <h2>What does it do?</h2>
          <p>Well, makes UI more optimized and ease of use. aswell supports all platforms (besides Education Edition) and proper support for controller.</p>
          <br>
          <p>This UI isn't a <b>client</b>, so this basically acts like your regular texture packs. this also does not modify or give you any advantages whatsoever.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="element-panel">
        <div class="element-panel-body">
          <h2>Compatibility</h2>
          <p>All in-game UI's are compatible. Although it does <b>not compatible with any UI packs that modifies pre-game UI.</b></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="element-panel">
        <div class="element-panel-body">
          <h2>Customizable</h2>
          <p>Collapse-UI offers some and customizability with the theme and layout.</p>
          <br>
          <p>You can change about how would UI look, e.g Red accents, backgrounds, etc. <b>Look for "Configuration" section in Installation page.</b></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
